&gt; &gt;&gt; If you&#39;re just starting with Heritrix, we recommend using 1.14.3.=

&gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; With the default configuration, crawling will generally stay on =
the 
&gt; &gt;&gt; sites defined by the seeds, but the crawler will go offsite to ge=
t URLs 
&gt; &gt;&gt; that appear necessary to render on-site pages (such as embedde=
d images, 
&gt; &gt;&gt; scripts, stylesheets, etc.). This behavior comes from the 
=
&gt; &gt;&gt; &#39;TransclusionDecideRule&#39; -- so removing that rule or setting its vario=
us 
&gt; &gt;&gt; &#39;*-hops&#39; limits to zero will prevent the offsite collection.
&gt; &gt;&gt;
=
&gt; &gt;&gt; On the other hand, if you do want necessary offsite resources, but fin=
d 
&gt; &gt;&gt; Heritrix sometimes going too many hops off, you could reduce those =

&gt; &gt;&gt; TransclusionDecideRule &#39;*-hops&#39; values without moving them to zero. 
=
&gt; &gt;&gt; Also, Heritrix always considers links found in Javascript or Flash to =
be 
&gt; &gt;&gt; like inline/embedded resources (because it can&#39;t tell the differen=
ce 
&gt; &gt;&gt; between those that load into the page, or only load on user naviga=
tion). 
&gt; &gt;&gt; So if you find the only reason Heritrix is wandering offsite i=
s such 
&gt; &gt;&gt; links, you could disable Javascript extraction (in the Extract=
orHTML and 
&gt; &gt;&gt; ExtractorJS) and Flash extraction (in ExtractorSWF).
